{"id": "gk99i5", "title": "API to load US senator stock trading data into Python", "selftext": " [u/pdwp90](https://www.reddit.com/u/pdwp90/) created a pretty cool visualization of [US senator trading activity](https://www.reddit.com/r/dataisbeautiful/comments/gjlvnd/buying_and_selling_of_stock_by_us_senators/).\n\nThere  is now an API available that loads the trading data from Quiver  Quantitative into Python for you to use. The code easily produces a list  of trades performed by senators in list or pandas DataFrame format.  Should be easy to use from there.\n\nYou can get the code by running the following code in your shell:\n\n`pip install senator_trading`\n\nThere is also a [github website](https://github.com/c-type/senator_trading):\n\nAfter installing senator\\_trading using pip you can run:\n\n`import senator_trading as st`\n\n`trades_obj = st.Trades() # this initializes a trades object`\n\n`all_trades_list = trades_obj.load_trades() # this creates a list of Trade objects`\n\n`all_trades_df = trades_obj.build_trade_df(all_trades_list) # a DataFrame of trades is created`\n\n`fig, ax = trades_obj.plot_trade_vol() # plots a figure of traded volume over tim`e\n\n&#x200B;\n\n&#x200B;\n\nhttps://preview.redd.it/9xjispx4mxy41.png?width=609&format=png&auto=webp&s=760fcdd5217ee2642da0717f6f988559dcea1aa3", "created_utc": 1589549888.0, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/gk99i5/api_to_load_us_senator_stock_trading_data_into/", "is_self": true}